I've added debug to print all instances (including terminated) prior to making the run instance request. In this test there are no instances to be shown in any state on the system. comments.body:
My original comment below, is not related to the reported issue, but I'll leave it here since it is a related problem. EUCA-4211 at least partially addresses the issue of private network index allocation in 3.3.0, but it looks like there is another cause (other than concurrency) for the issue that was not addressed.

This issue can occur when running (and presumably also when starting) more than one instance at a time and there are no other instances running using the security group.

Thanks [~sjones],
The request here is for (running) 2 instances, and no other instances are running in that security group. This is in line with your comment.
